Implement the following plan:

# Plan: Render the Chat Component

## Context

`Chat.svelte` is currently a stub that only renders `<h2>{chat.name}</h2>`. The PPD marks "Full message rendering" as the next remaining MVP deliverable. This plan replaces the stub with a real chat view: a sticky header showing the partner's info, and a scrollable message list with role-based bubble styling.

## Files to Change

| File | Action |
|---|---|
| `src/lib/time.ts` | **Create** — extract `formatTime` from Selector (DRY: needed in both Chat and Selector) |
| `src/lib/Selector.svelte` | **Edit** — replace inline `formatTime` with `import { formatTime } from './time.js'` |
| `src/lib/Chat.svelte` | **Replace** — full implementation (header + message list) |
| `src/lib/Chat.svelte.spec.ts` | **Create** — browser tests following Selector.svelte.spec.ts patterns |
| `src/routes/page.svelte.spec.ts` | **Edit** — update the broken `h2` heading check to match new header structure |

## Implementation (TDD order: tests first, then feature)

### 1. `src/lib/time.ts` (new)

```ts
/** Format a message time: HH:MM if today, else "Mon DD". */
export function formatTime(date: Date): string {
    const now = new Date();
    const sameDay =
        date.getFullYear() === now.getFullYear() &&
        date.getMonth() === now.getMonth() &&
        date.getDate() === now.getDate();
    if (sameDay) {
        return date.toLocaleTimeString([], { hour: '2-digit', minute: '2-digit' });
    }
    return date.toLocaleDateString([], { month: 'short', day: 'numeric' });
}
```

Then in `Selector.svelte`: remove the inline definition, add `import { formatTime } from './time.js';`.

### 2. `src/lib/Chat.svelte` — full component

**Script:**
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
    import { appState } from './state.svelte.js';
    import { formatTime } from './time.js';

    const chat = $derived(appState.chats[appState.currentlySelected]);

    let messagesEl: HTMLUListElement;

    // Scroll-lock: true = auto-follow new messages. Updated by the scroll listener
    // so we capture position before DOM changes, avoiding post-update timing issues.
    let scrollLocked = true;

    function onScroll() {
        if (!messagesEl) return;
        scrollLocked = messagesEl.scrollHeight - messagesEl.scrollTop - messagesEl.clientHeight < 16;
    }

    // Always start at the bottom when opening a different chat
    $effect(() => {
        appState.currentlySelected;
        scrollLocked = true;
    });

    // After each DOM update, scroll only if the user was already at the bottom
    $effect(() => {
        chat.messages.length;
        if (scrollLocked) messagesEl?.scrollTo({ top: messagesEl.scrollHeight });
    });
</script>
```

**Template** — uses `data-*` for role/status and semantic elements (`<header>`, `<figure>`, `<time>`) to keep classes minimal:
```svelte
<section class="chat">
    <header>
        <figure>
            <img src={chat.profilePicture} alt={chat.name} />
            <span data-status={chat.status}></span>
        </figure>
        <div>
            <strong>{chat.name}</strong>
            <small>{chat.statusText}</small>
        </div>
    </header>

    {#if chat.messages.length === 0}
        <p class="empty">No messages yet. Say something.</p>
    {:else}
        <ul bind:this={messagesEl} onscroll={onScroll}>
            {#each chat.messages as msg, i (i)}
                <li data-role={msg.role}>
                    {#if msg.role === 'partner'}
                        <img src={chat.profilePicture} alt={chat.name} />
                    {/if}
                    <p>
                        {msg.text}
                        <time datetime={msg.time.toISOString()}>{formatTime(msg.time)}</time>
                    </p>
                </li>
            {/each}
        </ul>
    {/if}
</section>
```

**CSS** — element + attribute selectors eliminate most class noise. Only `.chat` and `.empty` are classes:
```css
.chat { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
/* parent handles flex:1; overflow-y:auto via :global(.chat) */

header {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;
    padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
    background: white; position: sticky; top: 0;
}
header figure {
    position: relative; flex-shrink: 0; width: 40px; height: 40px; margin: 0;
}
header figure img {
    width: 40px; height: 40px; border-radius: 50%;
    object-fit: cover; background: #ccc;
}
header figure span {
    position: absolute; bottom: 1px; right: 1px;
    width: 10px; height: 10px; border-radius: 50%; border: 2px solid white;
}
/* Status colours via data attribute */
header figure span[data-status="active"]  { background: #4caf50; }
header figure span[data-status="away"]    { background: #ff9800; }
header figure span[data-status="busy"]    { background: #f44336; }
header figure span[data-status="offline"] { background: #9e9e9e; }
header strong { display: block; }
header small  { color: #555; }

ul { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 8px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; }

li { display: flex; align-items: flex-end; gap: 6px; }
li[data-role="user"]    { justify-content: flex-end; }
li[data-role="partner"] { justify-content: flex-start; }

li img { width: 32px; height: 32px; border-radius: 50%; background: #ccc; flex-shrink: 0; }

li p {
    max-width: 60%; margin: 0; padding: 6px 10px; border-radius: 12px;
    word-break: break-word;
}
li[data-role="user"] p    { background: #0084ff; color: white; border-bottom-right-radius: 2px; }
li[data-role="partner"] p { background: #e9e9eb; border-bottom-left-radius: 2px; }

time { display: block; font-size: 0.7em; opacity: 0.65; }

.empty { color: #999; font-style: italic; text-align: center; padding: 16px; }
```

Net class count: **2** (`.chat` required by parent; `.empty` for the empty state) vs ~14 in the original draft.

### 3. Write tests first (fail phase)

**`src/lib/Chat.svelte.spec.ts`** (new) — write these before implementing Chat:

Test groups (selectors updated to match data-* approach):
- **header**: partner name visible (`page.getByText`), `header figure img` present, `header figure span` present, `span[data-status="active"]` correct, status text visible
- **empty state**: `.empty` present when no messages, `ul` absent
- **messages**: all message texts render, `li[data-role="partner"]` count correct, `li[data-role="user"]` count correct, partner `<li>` contains `<img>`, user `<li>` does not, each `<li>` contains `<time>`
- **chat switching**: selecting a different chat updates the header name; messages from new chat appear

State setup pattern (from Selector tests):
```ts
beforeEach(() => {
    appState.currentlySelected = 0;
    appState.chats[0].messages = [];  // reset Claudia to clean state
});
```

**`src/routes/page.svelte.spec.ts`** — update the heading check now (it already fails after Chat changes):
```ts
// Before (h2 will be gone):
await expect.element(page.getByRole('heading', { name: 'Claudia', level: 2 })).toBeInTheDocument();

// After:
await expect.element(page.getByText('Claudia')).toBeInTheDocument();
```

**Verify tests compile and fail** (`vitest run src/lib/Chat.svelte.spec.ts`) before proceeding.

### 4. Implement `Chat.svelte` (make tests pass)

Replace the stub with the full component described above. Run `vitest run` to confirm all tests green.

## Verification

1. **Tests pass**: `vitest run` — Selector, page layout, and new Chat tests all green
2. **Visual check**: Ask user to start dev server and confirm:
   - Chat header shows "Claudia" with active status dot
   - Sending a message shows a right-aligned blue bubble
   - Selecting Jordan shows their seed message as a left-aligned gray bubble with avatar
   - New messages auto-scroll to bottom
3. **Update PPD**: Mark "Full message rendering" as complete


If you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/skye/.claude/projects/-Users-skye-workbench-claudia/ff151497-b06b-4fce-aca6-eeb2e86f578b.jsonl

